gr.interamerican.bo2.arch
Interface PersistenceUtility<PO>

Type Parameters:
PO - Class that is persisted by this PersistenceUtility.
All Known Subinterfaces:
PersistenceWorker<PO>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractHibernatePersistenceUtility, GenericHibernatePersistenceUtility, GenericHibernatePersistenceWorker, JdbcPersistenceWorker, LegacyPwAdapter
public interface PersistenceUtility<PO>

Persistence utility of a persistent class. This class undertakes persistence of the class PO to a data storage. The PersistenceWorker hides the technology specifics used for the underlying persistence implementation. The main methods of a PersistenceUtility are four methods used for CRUD operations.

  • store(po)
  • read(po)
  • update(po)
  • delete(po)
    • The name store is used instead of create, implying that the object is created in the JVM, and it is just stored in the database.
    All methods have only one argument, the object to persist. Ideally these methods will apply any change that would take place during the database operation to the argument it self. The implementation specifics of some persistence technologies make it hard to follow this rule always. For those cases, the CRUD methods of this interface return the object associated with the persistence operation.
